            content: "<p>The UK recorded its hottest June day on record on June 24, 2026, as an extreme heatwave swept across Western Europe. This extreme weather phenomenon also hit France, which recorded its hottest day in the country's modern weather recording history during the same period.</p><p>This heatwave added pressure to the UK's healthcare system already facing significant challenges due to concurrent resident doctor strikes. NHS England even described the combination of the heatwave, doctors' strikes, and World Cup 2026-related demand surge as a 'triple whammy' burdening emergency healthcare service capacity across various UK regions.</p><p>UK public health authorities issued health warnings regarding extreme temperatures, urging residents, particularly the elderly and vulnerable groups, to stay hydrated and avoid outdoor activities during the hottest hours. This phenomenon serves as a reminder of the global warming trend continuing to trigger new temperature records across various European regions in recent years.</p><p>This June 2026 temperature record has also sparked broader discussion about UK infrastructure readiness for increasingly frequent extreme weather, including urgent needs to strengthen cooling systems in public facilities and housing long designed for a relatively cooler climate.</p>",
